author: UMobile Athletics
title: The No. 6 University of Mobile women's soccer team picked up a 3-1 conference road win | AL.com
text:
The sixth-ranked University of Mobile women's soccer team out-shot Middle Georgia 31-1 on their way to a 3-1 Southern States Athletic Conference win Thursday evening.
The Knights scored first, just seven minutes in, but the Lady Rams scored the final three goals of the game, with Leah Corse heading home the equalizer in the 20th minute and Tyler-Rae Molloy notching the game-winner in the 78th minute.
Scoring Summary
7:22 – Middle Georgia – Micayla Crenshaw (assist by Chloe Handy)
20:02 – Mobile – Leah Corse (assist by Saskia Adriance)
78:36 – Mobile – Tyler-Rae Molloy (assist by LaTesha Fleming)
86:57 – Mobile – Katie Compton (assist by Savannah Rommel)
Numbers Game
9 – Katie Compton reclaims the team lead in goals with nine and points with 21
14 – Middle Georgia's Brooke Best came up with 14 stops in goal
19 – Mobile put 19 shots on frame, with Hebert, Compton and Molloy all putting four on target
31 – Mobile kept the pressure on all game with 31 shots, including 20 in the second half
Additional Notes
• This was Mobile's eighth game with 20+ shots, with a high of 44 coming v. Bethel
• The 19 shots on frame was the second most, behind 20 v. Bethel Oct. 3
• Mobile has scored multiple goals in 12 of 14 games, with a high of six twice
• Mobile has allowed one goal or less in 12 of 14 games as well
Next
Mobile (13-1, 4-1) visits Brewton-Parker Saturday at 1 p.m. for an SSAC contest.
